# Goal Description
Update the "Join Ecosystem" form to capture detailed specifications based on the user's chosen role (Farmer or Restaurant).

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend Modifications
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///c:/Users/DAYA%20ROSE/OneDrive/farmer-restaurant/index.html)
- Add a hidden "Farmer Specifications" section to the form:
  - Farm Size (e.g., Acres)
  - Key Produce/Dairy Types
- Add a hidden "Restaurant Specifications" section:
  - Cuisine Type
  - Estimated Weekly Organic Waste (kg/lbs)

#### [MODIFY] [styles.css](file:///c:/Users/DAYA%20ROSE/OneDrive/farmer-restaurant/styles.css)
- Add a `.hidden { display: none; }` utility class.
- Add specific styling for the new input fields (aligned with the existing glassmorphism aesthetic).

#### [MODIFY] [script.js](file:///c:/Users/DAYA%20ROSE/OneDrive/farmer-restaurant/script.js)
- Add an `onchange` event listener to the "Role" dropdown.
- When "Farmer" is selected, show the Farmer Specifications and hide the Restaurant ones (and vice versa).
- Ensure the JavaScript `FormData` capture still neatly packages these new fields into the JSON payload sent to the backend.

### Backend Validation (Optional Polish)
#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/DAYA%20ROSE/OneDrive/farmer-restaurant/server.js)
- *Note:* The backend already captures all `req.body` data, so no strict database schema changes are needed since it's saving straight to JSON, but we can log the new custom fields for clarity.

